ic symmetry which corresponds to the one studied by\nBonini and Feo; an existence of this exact symmetry itself does not imply a\nrestoration of supersymmetry in the continuum limit without any adjustment of\nparameters.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Dec 2004 06:57:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 14 Feb 2005 02:11:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
